 "contentEncoded": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/nathanbaker/4144871239/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2574/4144871239_d693e7a38d.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"416\" height=\"139\"></a></p>\n<p>Good morning, Nashville. That magical time of the year we call Football Season is upon us and the <a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/global/story.asp?s=12981918\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Titans kicked it off less-than-awesomely in Seattle on Saturday with a 20-18 loss</a>. But! Chris Johnson seems to be picking up right where he left off last season and <a href=\"http://www.fannation.com/truth_and_rumors/view/81938-vince-young-sues-friends-for-trademark\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.fannation.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">VY&#x2122;</a> wasn&#x2019;t looking too shabby either. Next time we see them, <a href=\"http://www.titansonline.com/schedule/season-schedule.html\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.titansonline.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">they&#x2019;ll be taking on the Arizona Cardinals at LP Field</a> and <a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/Global/story.asp?S=12727118\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">hopefully someone has fixed that sinkhole</a>!</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Be nice.</strong> <a href=\"http://www.newschannel5.com/global/story.asp?s=12983317\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.newschannel5.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">It&#x2019;s orientation time for most of the area colleges for the next week or two, which means we have a whole new crop of Nashvillians to woo with our wonderful city</a>. So if you find a bunch of lost-looking freshmen clogging up the line at your favorite coffee shop, cut &#x2018;em some slack. Welcome to Nashville, kids.</li>\n<li><strong>Pay as you throw.</strong> Metro will <a href=\"http://nashvillecitypaper.com/content/city-news/council-expected-pass-bill-charge-extra-trash?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed:+NashvilleCityPaper-LatestNews+(Nashville+City+Paper+-+Latest+News)&amp;utm_content=Google+Reader\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvillecitypaper.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">likely be passing a bill to start charging people who have too much trash to encourage better recycling practices</a>. Under the new law, known as &#x201C;pay as you throw,&#x201D; residences that use more than one trash bin would be facing a fine.</li>\n<li><strong>Bits &amp; pieces. </strong>An affluent neighborhood off of Granny White is <a href=\"http://nashvillecitypaper.com/content/city-news/neighborhood-still-crippled-flood-related-landslides?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed:+NashvilleCityPaper-LatestNews+(Nashville+City+Paper+-+Latest+News)&amp;utm_content=Google+Reader\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvillecitypaper.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">still in pretty bad shape from a flood-related landslide</a>, three months later &#x2026; <em><a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/article/20100816/NEWS01/8160319/-1/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Contributor</a></em><a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/article/20100816/NEWS01/8160319/-1/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\"> vendors are still raking in the paper sales</a> despite the heat &#x2026; <a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/article/20100816/BUSINESS01/8160338/Opry+Mills++return+after+flood+remains+mystery\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Opry Mills&#x2019; reopening date is still up in the air</a>, though some stores may open long before others &#x2026; The weather is going to be <a href=\"http://nashvillewx.com/2010/08/slightly-coolerslightly/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvillewx.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">slightly less hellish today</a> with the possibility of some cooler temperatures toward the end of the week thanks to a potential tropical storm &#x2026; Memphis is all Elvis&#x2019;d out today with mourners pouring in from all over to <a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/article/20100816/NEWS01/100816001/-1/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">commemorate the 33rd anniversary of his death</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n\n<p>No related posts.</p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<!--END .entry-content .article-->"
